init_text: When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The reason I choose a private box seat is because I want to be able to see everything that is going on.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I want to be able to see the people, the places, and the things that I will be doing in my next life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The film is about a little girl who is about to be born.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She is a very special little girl.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As the film continues, I start to notice that the little girl is very different from the other children.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She is very curious about the world around her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They tell her to stop asking questions.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I am so happy that I am not like the other kids.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I walk out of the theater and go to the concession stand.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I ask for some popcorn as well.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The lights dim again and the film resumes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The little girl is now a teenager.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She is still curious and still asking questions.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She asks, "What is the meaning of life?"
